WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Hexado' is a Workbench game played on an hexagonally shaped
board. The goal is to rotate bars so at least 3 bars are lined up
in the same direction, either horizontally or diagonally, as what
is shown on the bars.

  When 3 or more bars are lined up, those bars will be removed
from the board and you will get points depending on the number of
bars that were lined up.

  Sounds simple? There is one little complication: You cannot
click two or more times in a row on the same bar, as it will
rotate only once; you have to click on another bar before clicking
again on the former bar.

  ...Furthermore, as you progress in the game, from time to time,
some bars will randomly be removed from the board...

  Have fun!

